Emma has is organized three layers:
- Core, where the main stuff happens (database, mainloop, ...)
- Interfaces, the ones that communicates with the world (email, irc, wiki, lorea, ...)
- Modules, the actions and so for the assembly. That should be easy to hack and welcome for every developer.

You can get the documentation by:
$ epydoc emma
The folder 'html' will be created with the doc in it.

You can see the bug/feature/patch list by:
$ ditz
This command can be called anywhere inside this repository.
